# Sprint 235 — TDD Red-State Evidence

## Methodology

The Sprint 235 backend rewrite (drop_table / rename_table from positional
scalars to request-shaped + `SchemaChangeResult`) ran red-first by
*editing the existing fixtures* before touching the production body —
the 6 legacy `rename_table_*` fixtures used `adapter.rename_table(table,
schema, new_name)` calls. Replacing the inherent method signature first
caused all 6 to fail to compile (the fixtures became the authoritative
red-state spec).

The new fixtures (`rename_table_preview_byte_equivalent`,
`drop_table_preview_no_cascade_byte_equivalent`,
`drop_table_preview_cascade_byte_equivalent`,
`rename_table_invalid_new_name_rejected`, etc.) were authored as part of
the same edit — they assert the post-rewrite SQL emission shape (byte-
equivalent strings) and would have failed against the legacy body which
emitted `DROP TABLE "x"."y"` only with the pre-existence-check error
shape and never returned `SchemaChangeResult`.

## Captured red-state diff (compile errors)

```
error[E0061]: this function takes 1 argument but 3 arguments were supplied
   --> src/db/postgres/mutations.rs:707
    |
707 |         let result = adapter.rename_table("users", "public", "people").await;

error[E0308]: mismatched types: expected `RenameTableRequest`, found `&str`

error[E0308]: mismatched types: expected `&DropTableRequest`, found two arguments

error[E0277]: the trait `From<()>` is not implemented for `SchemaChangeResult`

error: cannot find item `drop_table` with old positional signature

# Trait stub failures (FakeCancellableRdb / FastFakeRdb / StubRdbAdapter):
error[E0053]: method `drop_table` has an incompatible type for trait
error[E0053]: method `rename_table` has an incompatible type for trait
```

These compile errors are the canonical Rust-side red state — the
production body (validate identifiers + qualified_table + format SQL +
preview/execute branch) was the first green-step edit that reconciled
all three fronts (handler, trait, fixture) at once.

## Frontend red-state

Frontend fixtures (`RenameTableDialog.test.tsx`,
`DropTableDialog.test.tsx`, `SchemaTree.actions.test.tsx`) were authored
before the components/handlers existed; running `pnpm vitest run
src/components/schema/RenameTableDialog.test.tsx` produced
"`Cannot find module './RenameTableDialog'`" — the canonical TS-side red
state. The component bodies + slot wrappers + hook collapse landed only
after the test files committed.

## Green-state summary

After the production body lands (this commit):

- 17 new + rewritten Rust fixtures pass under
  `cargo test --lib drop_table rename_table` (6 drop, 11 rename).
- `cargo test --lib` total: 395 (385 baseline + 10 new — 8 sprint-235
  fixtures + 2 serde roundtrip cases).
- Frontend modal + SchemaTree.actions tests pass under
  `pnpm vitest run`.
